+## Credentials — token only, never `gh`
+
+Fabro refreshes this sandbox's push credentials at node entry, so the
+`origin` remote carries a **freshly-minted installation token** that
+survives past the ~60-minute mint TTL. Both `git push` and the REST/
+GraphQL calls below use it. Extract it ONCE, and derive the repo coords,
+WITHOUT ever printing the token:
+
+```bash
+origin_url="$(git remote get-url origin)"
+# token is the password field of https://x-access-token:<TOKEN>@host/owner/repo(.git)
+GH_API_TOKEN="$(printf '%s' "$origin_url" | sed -nE 's#^https?://[^:]+:([^@]+)@.*#\1#p')"
+owner_repo="$(printf '%s' "$origin_url" | sed -nE 's#^https?://[^@]+@[^/]+/(.+)$#\1#p')"
+owner_repo="${owner_repo%.git}"   # strip a trailing .git (sed ERE has no non-greedy)
+owner="${owner_repo%%/*}"; repo="${owner_repo##*/}"
+# API base: honor $GITHUB_API_URL if set, else api.github.com (github.com host)
+api="${GITHUB_API_URL:-https://api.github.com}"
+```
+
+If `GH_API_TOKEN` comes out empty, `origin` has no inline token — STOP
+and use the needs-human protocol below (do NOT fall back to `gh`).
+NEVER `echo`/`printf` the token value; pass it only via `-H` below.
+
